==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: BUN
<hw>BUN</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[acronym]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>same as <col><b>blood urea nitrogen</b></col>; the concentration of
nitrogen in blood present in the form of urea; -- used as a measure of
kidney function.</def> <note>Blood usually contains 10 to 15 mg of
nitrogen per 100 ml in the form of urea. <au>Stedman.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

